          <h3>Conducting a Competitive AI Audit</h3>
          <p>
            Before investing in ChatGPT optimisation, map the competitive landscape. Build a query set representing the 30–50 most commercially relevant queries in your category. Run these queries in ChatGPT with web browsing enabled and record: which brands are cited for each query, how frequently each brand appears across the full query set, how each brand is described, and whether any brands consistently occupy the first citation position.
          </p>
          <p>
            This audit reveals which competitors have already invested in AI visibility (they will appear consistently across the query set), which queries are uncontested (where establishing citation would face minimal competition), and where your brand is being described inaccurately (a quick win through content correction).
          </p>
          <p>
            The brands that dominate these AI-generated answers are often not the same brands that dominate traditional search rankings. AI citation authority is a distinct competitive variable that has not yet been captured by traditional competitive intelligence tools. First-mover advantages in AI citation are available in many categories — but the window is narrowing as more brands invest in <a href="/generative-engine-optimisation/" class="text-accent-400 underline decoration-accent-500/30 underline-offset-2 hover:text-accent-300">generative engine optimisation</a>.
          </p>
        </div>
